ByChibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Nigeria’s COVID-19 death toll on Sunday hit 1,002 as the Centre for Disease Control reported 322 new confirmed cases. The report released by the Nigeria Centre for Disease control via its twitter handle has it that the new cases were recorded from 18 states as Lagos, Abuja and FCT came first, second and third with 130, 36 and 25 infections respectively. Others are; Edo-17;  Bayelsa, Ogun and Oyo-14  cases each; Anambra-13; Kaduna-12;  Ondo-11;  Abia-10;  Osun-6; Plateau and Kwara-5 each; Kano-4;  Ebonyi-3; Sokoto-2  and Borno-1 infection. The health agency further informed that the total confirmed COVID-19 cases have risen to 52,227 out of which 38,945 have been discharged. See how the states stand: By Abujah Racheal ABUJA - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has announced 653 new COVID-19 cases in the country as total infections from the virus rise to 35, 107. The NCDC made this known on its official twitter handle late on Saturday. The health agency said that as… July 19, 2020 In "Top Stories" By Abujah Racheal ABUJA - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has called on Nigerians to take preventive measures against the Coronavirus during the Eid-el-Kabir celebrations as the country recorded 481 new infections. The NCDC made this known on its official twitter handle on Thursday. The health agency said that… July 31, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA (Sundiata Post) - Nigeria has recorded 148 deaths from COVID-19 infections even as 248 new confirmed cases were added to the nation's swelling number of infections. Giving an update very late on Sunday, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) said Nigeria's COVID-19 infections stand at 4,399 cases.Lagos, which… May 11, 2020 In "Top Stories"